{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5bc4a306-7f60-411e-97d0-3a2a7381e8b7","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview any breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a96b484b-dbdc-4fb9-9b99-f03a881e431d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to explore their codebase since they've described the relevant files.","outputTokens":307,"requestId":"2828:239FAB:17C56FB:1A6B3D8:6A0285AB"},"id":"a3c680ac-6ea5-43c9-8ef2-90303ba39e07","timestamp":"2026-05-12T01:43:13.599Z","parentId":"9d148ea5-313d-4fc1-872b-381bb2496b57"}
